I'm hoping to see i11 as number 1 opening in coming WC, I am proud then :)

and we palyed this variant again

is there any trap if play 3?
now I had something in upper corner
he was tryng to defend with 35
and didnt want to give me tempo
I could put VCF threat to E13,
but I tried to get some more power first
but I lost quite much time with my tactics
finally I got one extrastone 48 for attack
but soon I didnt have much time left
finally I went to attack with 50
maybe play on F line first, then d12
who wants to show winning move here?
and made draw in time-trouble after 112 moves
nice win, so You good beat Aivo easily

white got nice threat from h5
i thought I can play to j11 in some moment,
but I couldnt find possible moment :)

now I was thinking again about taking point j11
well, Aivo is "brain" in Finnish language :)
seemed like a risky timing for j11
I think 34. k4 is way to win
now white is very passive again
but black doesnt have enough power to win either...
and it was too big shock for Aivo,
I have no time to save last game:(
semifinal of estonian cup 2004, second game, what was played some days ago :)

maybe a bit more interesting than i10, more chances for different games
so, he tries to leave to unknown fields
give up because renjuclass is over :)
its not so easy for white to win
but now Johancik was tired of game and made mistake
